#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:1
msgid "Adding Tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:4
msgid ""
"This page documents how to add test data while developing VTK with [Git][]. "
"See the [README](README.md) for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:9
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:12
msgid ""
"The workflow below depends on local hooks to function properly. Follow the "
"main [developer setup instructions](../develop_quickstart.md#initial-setup) "
"before proceeding.  In particular, run [SetupForDevelopment.sh][]:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:16
msgid "$ ./Utilities/SetupForDevelopment.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:20
msgid "Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:23
msgid ""
"Our workflow for adding data integrates with our standard Git [development "
"process](develop.md).  Start by [creating a topic](develop.md#create-a-"
"topic). Return here when you reach the \"edit files\" step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:28
msgid ""
"These instructions follow a typical use case of adding a new test with a "
"baseline image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:31
msgid "Writing new tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:33
msgid ""
"All new features that go into VTK must be accompanied by tests. This ensures "
"that the feature works on many platforms and that it will continue to work "
"as VTK evolves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:37
msgid ""
"Tests for the classes in each module of VTK are placed underneath the "
"module's Testing/<Language> subdirectory. Modules that the tests depend upon "
"beyond those that the module itself depends upon are declared with the "
"TEST_DEPENDS argument in the `vtk.module`   file. Test executables are added "
"to VTK's build system by naming them in the `CMakeLists.txt` files in each "
"Testing/<Language> directory. In those `CMakeLists`, standard "
"`add_executable()` + `add_test()` command pairs could be used, but the "
"following macros defined in `vtkModuleTesting.cmake` are preferable as they "
"consolidate multiple tests together, participate in VTK's modular build "
"scripts, and ensure consistency:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:37
msgid "<Language>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:47
msgid "{cmake:command}`vtk_add_test_cxx`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:48
msgid "{cmake:command}`vtk_add_test_mpi`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:49
msgid "{cmake:command}`vtk_add_test_python`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:51
msgid ""
"Tests indicate success to CTest by returning `EXIT_SUCCESS` (0) and failure "
"by returning `EXIT_FAILURE` (1). How the test determines what result to "
"return is up to the developer. VTK contains a number of utilities for this "
"task. For example, vtkRegressionTester is a helper class that does a fuzzy "
"comparison of images drawn by VTK against known good baseline images and "
"returns a metric that can be simply compared against a numeric threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:59
msgid ""
"Many tests require data files to run. The image comparison tests for example "
"need baseline images to compare against, and many tests open up one or more "
"files to visualize."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:63
msgid ""
"The source code and data file versions are kept in sync because the Testing/"
"Data directory contains, instead of the real files, similarly named files "
"which contain only the SHA512 hash of the matching data files. During the "
"build process, when CMake sees that a required data file is not available, "
"it downloads it into the directory defined by the ExternalData_OBJECT_STORES "
"cmake configuration entry. The test executables read all data from there. "
"The default setting for ExternalData_OBJECT_STORES is the ExternalData "
"directory underneath the VTK build tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:72
msgid ""
"To make a change to VTK that modifies or adds a new test data file, place "
"the new version in the Testing/Data or directory (for input data files) or "
"Module/Name/Testing/Data (for regression test images), and build (or run "
"cmake). CMake will do the work of moving the original out of the way and "
"replacing it with an SHA512 link file. When you push the new link file to "
"Gitlab, `git pre-commit` hooks push the original file up to Kitware's data "
"service, where everyone can retrieve it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:80
msgid "Add Test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:82
msgid "Write a new test, e.g."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:84
msgid "$ edit Some/Module/Testing/Cxx/MyTest.cxx\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:86
msgid "Edit the corresponding `CMakeLists.txt` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:88
msgid "$ edit Some/Module/Testing/Cxx/CMakeLists.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:90
msgid ""
"and add the test in a `vtk_add_test_...` call (which references baselines "
"automatically)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:93
msgid ""
"For tests not using such a call, reference the data file in an "
"`ExternalData_add_test` call.  Specify the file inside `DATA{...}` using a "
"path relative to the test directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:97
msgid ""
"$ edit Some/Module/Testing/Cxx/CMakeLists.txt\n"
"ExternalData_add_test(\"${_vtk_build_TEST_DATA_TARGET}\"\n"
"  NAME ${_vtk_build_test}Cxx-MyTest\n"
"  COMMAND <VTK_MODULE_NAME>CxxTests MyTest\n"
"          ... -V DATA{../Data/Baseline/MyTest.png,:} ...\n"
"  )\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:104
msgid ""
"Some tests may require additional files not referenced on the command line. "
"For these files, add references to a `vtk_module_test_data` call (usually in "
"the `Testing` parent directory). For example, adding `Testing/Data/lines."
"vtp` would mean adding `Data/lines.vtp` entry to the call (the `Testing` "
"directory is part of the path that is looked in automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:111
msgid ""
"vtk_module_test_data(\n"
"  Data/lines.vtp)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:114
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:116
msgid ""
"If the data file references other data files, e.g. `.mhd -> .raw`, read the "
"[ExternalData][] module documentation on \"associated\" files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:118
msgid ""
"Multiple baseline images and other series are handled automatically when the "
"reference ends in the `,:` option.  Read [ExternalData][] module "
"documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:124
msgid "Build and Run the Test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:126
msgid ""
"If you already have a data file, skip to the [next step](#add-data) to add "
"it. Otherwise, use the following steps to produce a test baseline image "
"file. We assume a build tree has been previously generated by CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:130
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:165
msgid "Switch to the build tree:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:132
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:167
msgid "$ cd ../VTK-build\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:134
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:169
msgid "Run CMake:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:136
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:171
msgid "$ cmake .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:138
msgid ""
"Since we have not yet created the baseline image data file, CMake will warn "
"that it does not exist but proceed to generate the test anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:142
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:185
msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:144
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:187
msgid "$ make\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:146
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:192
msgid "Run the test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:148
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:194
msgid "$ ctest -R MyTest\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:150
msgid "It will fail but place the baseline image in `Testing/Temporary`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:152
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:198
msgid "Switch back to the source tree:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:154
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:200
msgid "$ cd ../VTK\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:156
msgid "Add Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:158
msgid "Copy the data file into your local source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:160
msgid ""
"$ mkdir -p Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline\n"
"$ cp ../VTK-build/Testing/Temporary/MyTest.png Some/Module/Testing/Data/"
"Baseline\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:163
msgid "Run CMake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:173
msgid ""
"CMake will [move the original file](#externaldata).  Keep your own copy if "
"necessary.  See [below](#recover-data-file) to recover the original file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:177
msgid "During configuration CMake will display a message such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:179
msgid ""
"Linked Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512 to ExternalData "
"SHA512/...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:181
msgid ""
"This means that CMake converted the file into a data object referenced by a "
"\"content link\" named like the original file but with a `.sha512` "
"extension.  CMake also [renamed the original file](#externaldata)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:189
msgid ""
"During the build, the [ExternalData][] module will make the data file "
"available where the test expects to find it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:196
msgid "It should pass using the new data file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:202
msgid "Commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:204
msgid ""
"Continue to [create the topic](develop.md#create-a-topic) and edit other "
"files as necessary.  Add the content link and commit it along with the other "
"changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:208
msgid ""
"$ git add Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512\n"
"$ git add Some/Module/Testing/Data/CMakeLists.txt\n"
"$ git commit\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:212
msgid "The local `pre-commit` hook will display a message such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:214
msgid ""
"Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512: Added content to Git at "
"refs/data/SHA512/...\n"
"Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512: Added content to local "
"store at .ExternalData/SHA512/...\n"
"Content link Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512 -> ."
"ExternalData/SHA512/...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:218
msgid ""
"This means that the pre-commit hook recognized that the content link "
"references a new data object and [prepared it for upload](#pre-commit)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:221
msgid "Push"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:223
msgid ""
"Follow the instructions to [share the topic](develop.md#share-a-topic). When "
"you push it to GitLab for review using"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:226
msgid "$ git gitlab-push\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:228
msgid "part of the output will be of the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:230
msgid ""
"*       ...:refs/data/...      [new branch]\n"
"*       HEAD:refs/heads/my-topic  [new branch]\n"
"Pushed refs/data/... and removed local ref.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:234
msgid ""
"This means that the `git-gitlab-push` script pushed the topic and [uploaded "
"the data](#git-gitlab-push) it references."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:237
msgid "Options for `gitlab-push` include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:238
msgid "`--dry-run`: Report push that would occur without actually doing it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:239
msgid ""
"`--no-topic`: Push the data referenced by the topic but not the topic itself"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:241
msgid ""
"Note: One must `git gitlab-push` from the same work tree as was used to "
"create the commit.  Do not `git push` to another computer first and try to "
"push to GitLab from there because the data will not follow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:245
msgid "Building"
msgstr "建置"

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:248
msgid "Download"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:250
msgid ""
"For the test data to be downloaded and made available to the tests in your "
"build tree the `VTKData` target must be built.  One may build the target "
"directly, e.g. `make VTKData`, to obtain the data without a complete build.  "
"The output will be something like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:255
msgid ""
"-- Fetching \".../ExternalData/SHA512/...\"\n"
"-- [download 100% complete]\n"
"-- Downloaded object: \"VTK-build/ExternalData/Objects/SHA512/...\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:259
msgid "The downloaded files appear in `VTK-build/ExternalData` by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:261
msgid "Local Store"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:263
msgid ""
"It is possible to configure one or more local ExternalData object stores "
"shared among multiple builds.  Configure for each build the advanced cache "
"entry `ExternalData_OBJECT_STORES` to a directory on your local disk outside "
"all build trees, e.g. `/home/user/.ExternalData`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:268
msgid "$ cmake -DExternalData_OBJECT_STORES=/home/user/.ExternalData ../VTK\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:270
msgid ""
"The [ExternalData][] module will store downloaded objects in the local store "
"instead of the build tree.  Once an object has been downloaded by one build "
"it will persist in the local store for reuse by other builds without "
"downloading again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:275
msgid "Discussion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:278
msgid ""
"A VTK test data file is not stored in the main source tree under version "
"control.  Instead the source tree contains a \"content link\" that refers to "
"a data object by a hash of its content.  At build time the [ExternalData][] "
"module fetches data needed by enabled tests. This allows arbitrarily large "
"data to be added and removed without bloating the version control history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:285
msgid ""
"The above [workflow](#workflow) allows developers to add a new data file "
"almost as if committing it to the source tree.  The following subsections "
"discuss details of the workflow implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:289
msgid "ExternalData"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:291
msgid ""
"While [CMake runs](#run-cmake) the [ExternalData][] module evaluates [DATA{} "
"references](#add-test).  VTK sets in [vtkExternalData.cmake][] the "
"`ExternalData_LINK_CONTENT` option to `SHA512` to enable automatic "
"conversion of raw data files into content links.  When the module detects a "
"real data file in the source tree it performs the following transformation "
"as specified in the module documentation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:298
msgid "Compute the SHA512 hash of the file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:299
msgid "Store the `${hash}` in a file with the original name plus `.sha512`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:300
msgid "Rename the original file to `.ExternalData_SHA512_${hash}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:302
msgid ""
"The real data now sit in a file that we [tell Git to ignore](/.gitignore). "
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:305
msgid ""
"$ cat Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/.ExternalData_SHA512_477e6028* |"
"sha512sum\n"
"477e6028...  -\n"
"$ cat Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline/MyTest.png.sha512\n"
"477e6028...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:312
msgid "Recover Data File"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:314
msgid ""
"To recover the original file after running CMake but before committing, undo "
"the operation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:317
msgid ""
"$ cd Some/Module/Testing/Data/Baseline\n"
"$ mv .ExternalData_SHA512_$(cat MyTest.png.sha512) MyTest.png\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:320
msgid "pre-commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:322
msgid ""
"While [committing](#commit) a new or modified content link the [pre-commit]"
"[] hook moves the real data object from the `.ExternalData_SHA512_${hash}` "
"file left by the [ExternalData][] module to a local object repository stored "
"in a `.ExternalData` directory at the top of the source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:328
msgid ""
"The hook also uses Git plumbing commands to store the data object as a blob "
"in the local Git repository.  The blob is not referenced by the new commit "
"but instead by `refs/data/SHA512/${hash}`. This keeps the blob alive in the "
"local repository but does not add it to the project history.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:334
msgid ""
"$ git for-each-ref --format=\"%(refname)\" refs/data\n"
"refs/data/SHA512/477e6028...\n"
"$ git cat-file blob refs/data/SHA512/477e6028... | sha512sum\n"
"477e6028...  -\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:341
msgid "git gitlab-push"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:343
msgid ""
"The `git gitlab-push` command is actually an alias for the [git-gitlab-push]"
"[] script. In addition to pushing the topic branch to GitLab the script also "
"detects content links added or modified by the commits in the topic. It "
"reads the data object hashes from the content links and looks for matching "
"`refs/data/` entries in the local Git repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:350
msgid ""
"The script pushes the matching data objects to your VTK GitLab fork. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:353
msgid ""
"$ git gitlab-push --dry-run --no-topic\n"
"*       refs/data/SHA512/477e6028...:refs/data/SHA512/477e6028...   [new "
"branch]\n"
"Pushed refs/data/SHA512/477e6028... and removed local ref.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:357
msgid ""
"A GitLab webhook that triggers whenever a topic branch is pushed checks for "
"`refs/data/` in your VTK GitLab fork, fetches them, erases the refs from "
"your fork, and uploads them to a location that we tell ExternalData to "
"search in [vtkExternalData][] at build time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:362
msgid ""
"To verify that the data has been uploaded as expected, you may direct a web "
"browser to the location where ExternalData has uploaded the files. For VTK, "
"that location is currently `http://www.vtk.org/files/ExternalData/SHA512/"
"XXXX` where `XXXX` is the complete SHA512 hash stored in the content link "
"file (e.g., the text in `MyTest.png.sha512`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:371
msgid "Publishing Data for an External Branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:373
msgid ""
"The above [workflow](#workflow) works well for developers working on a "
"single machine to contribute changes directly to upstream VTK.  When working "
"in an external branch of VTK, perhaps during a long-term topic development "
"effort, data objects need to be published separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:378
msgid ""
"The workflow for adding data to an external branch of VTK is the same as the "
"above through the [commit](#commit) step, but diverges at the [push](#push) "
"step because one will push to a separate repository. Our ExternalData "
"infrastructure intentionally hides the real data files from Git so only the "
"content links (`.sha512` files) will be pushed. The real data objects will "
"still be left in the `.ExternalData/SHA512` directory at the top of the VTK "
"source tree by the [pre-commit](#pre-commit) hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:387
msgid ""
"The `.ExternalData` directory must be published somewhere visible to other "
"machines that want to use the data, such as on a web server. Once that is "
"done then other machines can be told where to look for the data, e.g."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:392
msgid ""
"cmake ../VTK \"-DExternalData_URL_TEMPLATES=https://username.github.io/VTK/"
"ExternalData/%(algo)/%(hash)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:394
msgid ""
"In this example we assume the files are published on a [Github Pages][] `gh-"
"pages` branch in `username`'s fork of VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/test.md:397
msgid ""
"Within the `gh-pages` branch the files are placed at `ExternalData/SHA512/"
"$sha512sum` where `$sha512sum` is the SHA512 hash of the content (these are "
"the same names they have in the `.ExternalData` directory in the original "
"source tree)."
msgstr ""
